President Obama spoke with Prime Minister Cameron of the United Kingdom about the shoot-down of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17. They both agreed that an independent international investigation needs to start immediately and that all countries should ensure secure access to the crash site. They also discussed the recent actions taken by the US and EU to increase pressure on Russia and agreed to take further action if Russia fails to de-escalate the situation. The leaders also discussed the situation in Gaza and agreed that Israel has the right to defend itself. They emphasized the need for a ceasefire and expressed concern about further escalation and loss of innocent lives. Additionally, they talked about the P5+1 talks with Iran and agreed to continue efforts to negotiate a comprehensive agreement that ensures Iran's nuclear activities are peaceful.